# 📊 Finance Dashboard Project

Welcome to my Data Science portfolio! This project explores how small business financial data can be analyzed using Python for insight-driven decision-making.

---

## 🔍 Project Overview

This notebook analyzes simulated monthly revenue and expense data to:
- Track profit trends over time
- Visualize key performance indicators
- Calculate profit margins
- Forecast future revenue using linear regression

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Technologies Used

- **Python**
- **Pandas** for data manipulation  
- **Matplotlib & Seaborn** for visualization  
- **Scikit-learn** for simple forecasting  
- **Google Colab** for development

---

## 📈 Key Visuals

- Line plot of monthly revenue and expenses
- Bar chart showing profit margins by month
- Forecast of next quarter’s revenue based on trends

---

## 📁 Dataset

This project uses **mock financial data** for educational and portfolio purposes. The dataset includes:
- Monthly Revenue
- Monthly Expenses
- Calculated Profit and Profit Margins

---

## 🚀 What I Learned

- Visual storytelling with data
- Hands-on practice with dataframes and plots
- Applying machine learning basics (regression) to financial data

---

## 🧠 Future Plans

- Integrate real-world QuickBooks exports  
- Build an interactive dashboard using Streamlit or Power BI  
- Expand forecasting models with time series data

